Popular Nigerian music star Oluwatobiloba Daniel Anidugbe aka Kizz Daniel has been announced as securing two brand endorsements. The singer will join BBNaija’s Erica Nlewedim as the face of Nigeria Breweries’ brands, Legend Extra Stout and Star Radler. Daniel is expected to play an important role in strengthening the presence of the brands across Nigeria.   Nkechi Blessing, husband fight dirty amid breakup     Someone gave me N3m for being a good girl – Ese Eriata     Ada Karl calls out Tonto Dikeh over alleged 15-year- debt   Excited about inking the deal, the ‘Woju’ singer said: “Legend Extra Stout and Star Radler are names that speak for themselves and I am excited to be working with both of them. I feel honored to be part of the process in terms of storytelling that inspires millions of people.” Daniel inked the deal at a cocktail event that preceded the Legend/Star Radler ‘We’re Outside’ Mix Party. Throughout the partnership, Kizz Daniel will be spearheading various innovative campaigns that align with both brands’ ideals that encourage authenticity and originality as well as fun and excitement. The campaign, which is expected to take several creative routes will amplify the brand’s exceptional qualities that allude to the use of the finest ingredients. The campaign will be released on both online and offline platforms.